caption: Hello to all Romanians from France and everywhere, I noticed a not very pleasant phenomenon. From (escu turned into esco) George Enescu is engraved on the grave as George Enesco? Why? Are we ashamed of our original Romanian origin???  A Bessarabian Roman by the way.
We thank those who marked his grave on the map! It is cared for and caressed by the sun's rays. Eternal gratitude to the great Romanian artist!
Have someone label the place of the grave on the sign at the entrance to the cemetery.

username: Success - UNMB - International GrandPrix of Romania
